olive oil
2 potato
1 packet Dill & Parsley Mayonnaise
1 sachet Louisiana spice blend
1 packet chicken thigh
1 packet BBQ sauce
1 stalk celery
1 pear
1 bag Shredded Cabbage Mix
drizzle vinegar (rice wine or white wine)

• Boil the kettle. Peel potato, then cut into bite-sized chunks.
• Half-fill a medium saucepan with boiling water, season with salt and bring to the boil.
• Cook potato in boiling water, over high heat, until easily pierced with a fork, 12-15 minutes.
• Drain and return to the pan. Allow to cool slightly, then add dill & parsley mayonnaise. Toss to combine. Season to taste.

Little cooks: Help stir the mayo through the potato! Careful, it's hot!

• SPICY! This is a mild spice blend, but use less if you're sensitive to heat! Meanwhile, combine Louisiana spice blend and a drizzle of olive oil in a medium bowl. Add chicken thigh and turn to coat.
• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Cook chicken, turning occasionally, until browned and cooked through,
14-16 minutes.
• Remove pan from heat, then add BBQ sauce, turning chicken to coat.

TIP: Chicken is cooked through when it's no longer pink inside.

• Meanwhile, thinly slice celery and pear.
• In a large bowl, combine celery, pear, shredded cabbage mix and a drizzle of vinegar and olive oil. Season to taste.

Little cooks: Take the lead by tossing the salad!

• Slice BBQ chicken.
• Divide creamy potato salad, pear slaw and chicken between plates. Enjoy!